title: CSE 2431 - Systems II: Introduction to Operating Systems
description: Introduction to operating system concepts: process, CPU scheduling, memory management, file system and storage, and multi-threaded programming.Prereq: 2421 (360); or 2451 (459.21), and ECE 2560 (265). Not open to students with credit for 5431 (660).
professors: Feng Qin,Yinqian Zhang,Doreen Close,Gojko Babic,Nathaniel Morris,George Green,Adam Champion
